@NODE "mail_0" " 24bit images/gtshapes in blitz (image.include) "
From: Thilo Köhler <koehlerthilo@...>
Date: 01-26-02 15:30:21
Subject: @{b}24bit images/gtshapes in blitz (image.include)@{ub}

Hi all!

It is done.
Here is the include file if you want to use
24bit (or whatever you want) images in your
Blitz programs. You can also convert them into
a blitz shape and use it with GTShape.

It uses datatypes for loading images, so you can
have any fileformat which has a datatype installed.
(e.g. iff, jpg, gif, pcx, bmp)

Drawbacks:
No real transparency is povided, because the shapes
are remapped and it is very unlikely that your shapes backgroundcolor
will be mapped to color 0 which is turned into transparency with
"makecookie". Maybe someone has an idea how to do this.

It uses guigfx (and render) library. So if you want to use it
you have to remake your deflibs with the guigfx.library1 included,
or create your own with the .fd file from the guigfx archive (Aminet).
(beware of libclashes !!!)

The include has to be regarded as alpha version, so maybe
there are some bugs or room for improvement, any suggestions are
welcome.

Have fun,

Thilo

P.S. And don't forget to set the right pathes for the include files,

@{fg shine}There should be a file mail_0/image_include.lha included with this guide.@{fg text}
@ENDNODE

