Subject: @{b}Re: Devices@{ub}

Hello amorel

No stuff is too complex for me!!!  ;-)
Try my sourcecode.
Sorry that I had not the time to document it.

Example would be:
_______________________________________________ BEGIN
if midiport_open {mp.w,"serial.device",unit.w}
  succ.w = midiport_write {mp.w,data_ptr.l, bytelength.l}
  midiport_close {mp.w}
End If
End
_______________________________________________ END

You can open as many midiports (=serial.device with 31250 baud)
as you have defined with #max_midiports.
It does not matter if you open the same device with
the same unit twice with several mp.w numbers,
it will be recognized correctly and handled correctly
if you close them.
Sorry that there is no midiport_read {} command, but it should
be easy to implement.
Advantage to the blitzcommands is that the data is send asynchron,
that means midiport_write {} returns immideately and you can go on
while your data is being sent.
It also works with different devices, e.g. 
