To create a filled box use the command Boxf x1,y1,x2,y2,colour.
You can use this command with new values to zoom +/- the box, but use a Cls
[colour] between every drawing to clear the used bitmap. You should need to
use double-buffered display.
For a filled circle, use the command Circlef x,y,radius[,y radius],colour as
above.
What is a T object?

Polyf numpoints,*coords.w,colour[,colour2]
is a command to draw filled polygons (use Poly for non-filled polys). You
must feed it with a pointer type array (a list of values, all referenced by
one word, like a variable), that contains all the coordinates (x,y) of the
points.

To learn the basics of BlitzBasic (now AmiBlitz, thanking to the great work
of Bernd Roesch, and the support mainly by David McMinn and all the
blitz-list gang), you should read its manual (you should have it, if your
copy is original...). I think there is an AmigaGuide version of the manual
somewhere (on blitz2000 site? I forget the url everytime I need it, so ask
to David McMinn).

