Like this:

Dim points.w(8) ; Allows 4 points to be defined
points(0) = 20 : points(1) = 20
points(2) = 120 : points(3) = 20
points(4) = 120 : points(5) = 80
points(6) = 20 : points(7) = 80
PolyF 4,&points(0),3

Of course, you will need to have created a bitmap to draw onto.

The colour2 parameter, IIRC allows you to plot the polygon in a different
colour if the points are in anti-clockwise order. You can also set this colour2
parameter to be -1 and the polygon will not be drawn
at all if the points are anti-clockwise.

