Firstly, in your event waiting loop, add the blitz command EventWindow that
return the window object number in where the event occurs.
Then check RawKey that returns the RAW keycode of the last pressed button.
RAW means that this value doesn't worry about keyboard mapping,  as this
command (as far as I remember - already exists AFAIR?) works in absolute
way, not relative. Example: if you press the 'z' key on a qwerty keyboard
RawKey returns a different value than in a qzerty one.
If you want to check for qualifiers, simply use Qualifier command.
This is a quick overview of what I do usually for my progs, and it works
fine! Use the downscore '_' char before the letter on a GadTools button, and
you get a nice interface. The only thing which works bad is the RawKey
function, that doesn't support keymapping. You should use os function to do
the thing.
