Hi there, Lewis

On 03-Jan-02, you said:

LB> Got an MUI interface on the go, using MUIBitmapObject to make some buttons
LB> that remap easily. question is how can I give them hotkeys?

OK, sorry it's taken a little time to get back to you on this, but here's your
answer.

Suppose you have the notification on your image button set up as:-

MUINotifyApp Obj,#MUIA_Pressed,0,#ID_BUTTONPRESSED

You would set your hotkey up as follows (the example uses the "b" key):-

MUINotifyApp Window,#MUIA_Window_InputEvent,"b",#ID_BUTTONPRESSED

Note that the event isn't allocated to your button, but to your host window. By
specifying the same return ID you ensure that the hotkey will call the same
routine.

If your notification is set to react on another MUI object, then simply set the
hotkey notification up the same way.

According to the MUI developer docs, this should only be used for the odd
hotkey, and subclasses should be used in general, but using subclasses for
hotkey events doesn't seem to work with EFMUI.library where hotkeys are not
directly supported by the Blitz command :o/

Nevertheless, I've tested my method, and it works.

Regards



